<paragraph id="8BE3860FFFE5FFE8FF76FA0E0420F888" blockId="9.[167,779,1351,2091]" pageId="9" pageNumber="488">
<emphasis id="B9285A1DFFE5FFE8FF76FA0E0466F9E5" bold="true" box="[168,330,1525,1549]" pageId="9" pageNumber="488">Identification.</emphasis>
Plants green, brownish to brown (when dry), ca. 
<quantity id="4CA42BEAFFE5FFE8FECCF9E30479F9C7" box="[274,341,1560,1584]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="9" pageNumber="488" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
wide. Ventral merophyte of 5–8 cells wide. Leaves suberect to convoluted when dry, widely spreading and convex when moist, imbricate, suborbicular, apex rounded, slightly plane, margin entire; median cells elongated, trigones cordate, cuticle smooth. Lobules ovate, 1/2‒1/3 lobe length, apex oblique, with 1 tooth. Underleaves contiguous to imbricate, entire, 4 × stem width, base rounded, apex truncate to rounded, margin entire. Perianth immersed to 1/3 emergent, obovate, 4 or 5-keeled.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE3860FFFE5FFE8FF10F89107C5F7C3" blockId="9.[167,779,1351,2091]" pageId="9" pageNumber="488">
The pantropical genus 
<taxonomicName id="4C5CFD8CFFE5FFE8FE0BF8910784F86A" authorityName="Verdoorn" authorityYear="1933" box="[469,680,1898,1922]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Schiffneriolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="9" pageNumber="488" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9285A1DFFE5FFE8FE0BF8910784F86A" box="[469,680,1898,1922]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="488">Schiffneriolejeunea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is comprised of 14 species, of which only two were recorded in 
<collectingCountry id="F34BC69FFFE5FFE8FF76F85605C7F82D" box="[168,235,1965,1989]" name="Brazil" pageId="9" pageNumber="488">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C5CFD8CFFE5FFE8FF2BF8550457F82D" box="[245,379,1965,1989]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Schiffneriolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="9" pageNumber="488" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="polycarpa">
<emphasis id="B9285A1DFFE5FFE8FF2BF8550457F82D" box="[245,379,1965,1989]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="488">S. polycarpa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C5CFD8CFFE5FFE8FE74F8550627F82D" authority="Gradst. Differences" authorityName="Gradst. Differences" box="[426,779,1965,1989]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Schiffneriolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="9" pageNumber="488" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="species" species="amazonica">
<emphasis id="B9285A1DFFE5FFE8FE74F855071AF82D" box="[426,566,1966,1989]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="488">S. amazonica</emphasis>
Gradst. Differences
</taxonomicName>
between these species are mainly in the leaf lobule; see the keys for 
<taxonomicName id="4C5CFD8CFFE5FFE8FEECF80A072EF7E1" authorityName="Verdoorn" authorityYear="1933" box="[306,514,2033,2057]" class="Jungermanniopsida" family="Lejeuneaceae" genus="Schiffneriolejeunea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Porellales" pageId="9" pageNumber="488" phylum="Marchantiophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9285A1DFFE5FFE8FEECF80A072EF7E1" box="[306,514,2033,2057]" italics="true" pageId="9" pageNumber="488">Schiffneriolejeunea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation id="EFCDFBFEFFE5FFE8FDF2F80A05C1F7C3" author="Gradstein SR &amp; Costa DP" pageId="9" pageNumber="488" pagination="1 - 318" refId="ref11527" refString="Gradstein SR, Costa DP (2003) The Hepaticae and Anthocerotae of Brazil. Memoirs of the New York Botanical Garden 87: 1 - 318." type="journal article" year="2003">Gradstein and Costa (2003)</bibRefCitation>
and 
